			<title>Deus Ex: Mankind Divided Announced</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?77777-Deus-Ex-Mankind-Divided-Announced&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2015 09:11:57 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[I generally like to post trailers all in the yearly and monthly release threads, but a release date hasn't been announced for this yet, and I figure it might be something most of you will want to know about. 
 
Square/Eidos had this weird interactive event website teasing a new game, which ended up...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I generally like to post trailers all in the yearly and monthly release threads, but a release date hasn't been announced for this yet, and I figure it might be something most of you will want to know about.<br />
<br />
Square/Eidos had this weird interactive event website teasing a new game, which ended up being revealed as the next Deus Ex. It has been revealed to be Game Informer's cover story for the month (as one of the few print magazines for games left, they plan these reveals well in advance). I honestly did not follow this stuff that closely, beyond waiting for a trailer to be posted.<br />
<br />
The only thing I can say with any certainty, and the most important takeaway, is that it is a direct sequel to Human Revolution and features the return of Adam Jensen. The trailer even has direct allusions to the ending of the first game. <br />
<br />
This is a big win for fans of the franchise. Turning IPs into mobile or mmo games and leaving their core audience behind is very common these days. I wasn't sure if we would even get a direct sequel. I was expecting a crappy mmo wannabe like Square is doing with other Eidos properties.<br />
<br />
The trailer itself is pretty good, but it doesn't compare to the trailer for Human Revolution in my opinion. Still pretty exciting though.<br />
<br />

