			<title><![CDATA[April '15 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?77747-April-15-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2015 02:37:55 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>If March was a flood of new game releases, April is pretty barren in comparison. Even the deluge of PS3 Japanese games has slowed to a trickle. There are certainly a few things to look forward to, but most of us will likely find this time better spent playing the things we bought last month. 
...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>If March was a flood of new game releases, April is pretty barren in comparison. Even the deluge of PS3 Japanese games has slowed to a trickle. There are certainly a few things to look forward to, but most of us will likely find this time better spent playing the things we bought last month.<br />
<br />
There is really only one big new release coming this month, and that's <b>Mortal Kombat X</b>. You should already know if this is the sort of thing that appeals to you or not. The gratuitous violence is being fully embraced, with some of the most disgusting fatalities yet. Whether you like going :wtf: or want to be a cool kid that pretends it doesn't bother you, your bases are covered.<br />
<br />
The Double Fine kickstarted adventure game <b>Broken Age</b> is also set to be finally finished this month, with Sony platforms getting ports of the complete package. I assume those of us with part 1 get part 2 for free, but haven't been following development that closely to say for sure.<br />
<br />
The 3DS is getting a decent month, with a port of <b>Xenoblade</b> being the main attraction. It's very important to know that you need the new 3DS sku (literally named &quot;New 3DS&quot; in stores) to be able to play it, as it has a faster cpu.<br />
<br />
Sony platforms in general are getting a lot of ports of games from other platforms as part of their Spring sale I mentioned last month. The only fully original game for the PS4 this month is <b>Omega Quintet</b>, a jrpg from Compile Heart, also known as the B(or C?) team of jrpgs. Be aware that the game is idol themed, so unless you are into that stuff, you might want to just pick up Type 0 from last month instead. FYI: idols = teen pop stars that sing and dance. <br />
<br />
Both new platforms (PS4 and Xone) are getting ports of <b>Dark Souls 2</b>. I do not know if they fixed the lighting engine. It might be interesting to see how this is, but I get the feeling it's mostly going to appeal to xbox users who can't play Bloodborne.<br />
<br />
<br />
Finally, as far as I am aware <b>Mighty No 9</b> is supposed to come out this month, but being a digital game, I'll believe it when I see it. This is the spiritual successor to Megaman that was kickstarted awhile back. It should be pretty good.<br />
<br />
<br />
